Happy Friday! Start the weekend off right with an epic trivia game on Gimkit! All are welcomed! Please follow the directions below to access this epic game of trivia.

Gimkit can be played on a computer, tablet or cellphone.

Go to gimkit.com/play
Enter code: 16938

Enter the game by typing in your first name or initials. Any inappropriate names will be sent back to try again!

The game will begin at 2 pm. If you are having any difficulties, please email Mr. Korzen at bkorzen@mtplcsd.org. Good luck and may the odds be ever in your favor.

Important Message Regarding District Closure Plans -

The Mount Pleasant Central School District will be using two emergency closure days to close schools on Monday, March 16, 2020 and Tuesday, March 17, 2020.

It is highly likely at that after these two days there will be an extension of the closure. We urge families to prepare for such.

Please visit https://www.mtplcsd.org/coronavirus_precautions to read the letter from Dr. Kotes to the community.

Stay safe and please practice social distancing. If we all work together, we can make a difference.

Westlake advances to the County Center after 42 years.

Wear your Blue & White to show your pride.

Westlake vs Hastings

post_text:
The Multi-Cultural Committee of Mount Pleasant invites you to submit your recipes to their annual cookbook:

Please keep the recipes coming...we are extending the deadline to receive recipes until November 15th. We are accepting recipes while we work on soliciting advertisement space from local restaurants and businesses. Yes, we are offering ad space in our cookbook! Advertisement offering details to follow, however, in the meantime please send in the recipes.

Please note the recipe book will be sold District Wide AND we've decided to accept recipes from school parents/families grade K-12. Please consider participating as we hope that it will become a wonderful addition to our kitchen for years to come.

See flyer for details.

Dear Parents and Guardians,

The lock-out at CES, WMS and WHS has now been lifted. The situation was contained to EF Academy. All police supervisors have reconciled that it is safe for us to dismiss our students. We will maintain a police presence through and including dismissal. Intermittently, residents may hear helicopter surveillance around the area of EF Academy.

Dismissal at WMS/WHS will occur at approximately 2:40 - 2:45. Dismissal at CES will occur at approximately 3:20 - 3:25.

ALL AFTER SCHOOL ACTIVITIES, INCLUDING ATHLETICS, WILL BE CANCELED. The Inspire program at Hawthorne Elementary will continue as usual.

Thank you.

Attention Westlake Middle School Parents/Caregivers:

If you have an Optimum email address, you may not be receiving important emails from Dr. Bronstein and Mrs. Parrottino.

Optimum’s mail servers are universally flagging email from Adam Bronstein and Christine Parrottino as “spam”, therefore anyone with an address at optonline.net or optimum.net will not receive emails sent to parents. When contacted, Optimum said that each individual will need to contact Optimum directly to report WMS as a safe sender.
Due to the fact that the problem resides on the Optimum servers, we are unable to resolve the problem on our end.

We sincerely apologize for the inconvenience this may have caused. Please reach out to the WMS office at 914-769-8540 if you continue to have questions or concerns.

post_text: It’s Wellness Day at Columbus Elementary! Students took part in several workshops focusing on physical and emotional wellness. Presentations included art, speed and agility, nutrition, yoga, Reiki sound, therapy dogs, self esteem and growth mind set, aerobics, martial arts, first aid, inquisitive minds, and water safety. Harley, the police search dog, was a big hit with the kids! It was a great way to end a busy week. Thanks to Christine Cazes for organizing the amazing day!

Each spring, the Congressional Institute and Members of the House of Representatives sponsor an art competition in which one high school student artist’s work from each participating Congressional District is selected and displayed in the halls of the U.S. Capitol. Congratulations to both Aimee Holland and Hillary Avila, class of 2021 who submitted their work to this National Competition.

At a reception on Monday, May 6th Congresswoman Nita Lowey announced the winners for this years competition. Congratulations to Hillary Avila, a student in Claudia Papazian’s Drawing and Painting class, for winning this prestigious award. Hillary and her family will travel to Washington D.C. for the National reception where her work will hang in the halls of Congress for the remainder of the year!

Congratulations to the WHS Science Olympiad team led by WMS/WHS science teachers Tom Hall and Ray Sczcerba. They competed last weekend in the NYS Lower Hudson Valley Science Olympiad at Byram Hills High School where they placed 20th out of 50 teams.

In "Herpetology", Elisabeth Carpinelli and Oliva Cartano took home 10th place. In "Sounds of Music", Matheus Louzada and Pranav Vadapalli took home 9th place. In "Forensics", Olivia Eng and Olivia Cartano took home 4th place. In "Elastic Gliders", Paul Gschneidner and Caleb Levitt took home 4th place.

Congratulations to everyone for their hard work!

If you have not had the opportunity to respond to the Outdoor Facilities Questionnaire, here is the information again.

The Board of Education has been asked to consider upgrading the outdoor athletic facilities on the Westlake campus.

A special meeting was held on Thursday, January 17th, 2019 for the Board to hear the public's opinion on the project before they consider whether to move forward. A video recording of the meeting can be found on our district website at www.mtplcsd.org, under the Board of Education tab.

If you did not have the opportunity to share your thoughts at the meeting, or would like to provide your feedback, please take a moment to respond to our Outdoor Athletic Facilities Questionnaire. The survey will be completely anonymous and the district will not be able to delineate your name or email in any way. Your responses will be shared with the Superintendent and the Board of Education.

Your feedback is important to us. Thank you for time.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScyHwgFRz8EXox03xriDw8ftfNnOwXz1y7OsrVB9y3QjwjATA/viewform?usp=sf_link

post_text: The Westlake community welcomes our neighbors from Tappan Zee High School.
shared_text:
South Orangetown Central School District
December 18, 2018 at 11:23 PM ·

The Tappan Zee High School Master Scheduling Inquiry Team made its third school visit today. "Principal Schenker and the students and faculty at Mount Pleasant Central School District's Westlake High School were gracious hosts for our team of 15 members," reports Principal Dr. Jennifer Amos. "We visited classes and engaged in fruitful dialogue with the Westlake team about their academic experiences in their block schedule."

During each visit, team members speak with the three key stakeholder groups about how their high school’s schedule impacts students’ stress level, choice and achievement; faculty instructional practices, collaboration and culture; and, facilities, food service and staffing requirements.

For links to previous stories regarding the Master Scheduling Inquiry Team's work, view this story online: http://blogs.socsd.org/2016socsd/2018/12/18/master-scheduling-inquiry-team-visits-westlake-hs/
